{"key":"processedPost-9004902","value":{"id":9004902,"first":9002662,"last":9004902,"when":1222741252,"utime":"09/30/08 05:20 AM","content":"I absolutely hate the pillow case tek.&nbsp; The excess moisture rarely drains out entirely by gravity, leaving it too wet unless you squeeze it out afterwards.&nbsp; In addition, you leave the substrate hanging overnight exposed to mold spores, which land on your pasteurized substrate material and grow.<br /><br />I'd suggest pasteurizing in mason jars in a large pot of water.&nbsp; This way, you get the moisture content right before you pasteurize, and you can even seal up the jars to prevent the entry of competitor organisms.<br />RR","title":"Re: Coir/manure mix cobweb and trich question","forum":"Mushroom Cultivation"}}